      <p>Education: Marischal College, Aberdeen. MA (1844)</p>
      <p>Career: Education Department, Bombay Presidency (1846); Professor of Mathematics, Royal College of Mauritius (1848); founded the Mauritius Meteorological Society (1851); in charge of the Mauritius Government Observatory (1862-1896); returned to England (1896)</p>
      <p>Honours: CMG 1886</p>
